Moreno on Coutinho: &quot;I have told him: 'Brother, don&rsquo;t go'. I can&rsquo;t tell you what he said to me here, of course, because it&rsquo;s something that&rsquo;s very personal.&quot;<br />
<br />
Moreno on Coutinho: &quot;I want him to stay. If I get to decide, Philippe&rsquo;s not going. But I can&rsquo;t interfere. It&rsquo;s Liverpool, Barcelona and him, and they decide.&quot;

Pellegrino on his time at Liverpool: &ldquo;I had good memories from this moment because we won the Champions League and I was in this group.&quot;<br />
<br />
Pellegrino on his time at Liverpool: &ldquo;After as a coach it was my first experience also to be in contact with professional players with Rafa Benitez, and I can say I am really grateful for those days, for those times.&rdquo;

Maurcio Pellegrino on Anfield return: &ldquo;It will be really, really special, and not just about football because I had been living there with my family, my children in the school, in the streets.&quot;<br />
<br />
Pellegrino on Anfield return: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s not just about football, it&rsquo;s about the people and I have got good memories, I know the people that is working there. My only words is to be grateful.&rdquo;

Klopp on Salah: &quot;He could have scored even more. He's a fantastic player and can still improve.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp on Lallana: &quot;There is no need to rush it, we have 3 games next week. Anyone who knows Adam will know how ready he is.&quot;

Klopp says medical staff gave him a clean bill of health this week - but warned him to avoid losing matches. &ldquo;It is not that someone should think I have to go back into hospital tomorrow. I told the players the doctor said the only thing that can kill me is if we lose games!&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;It was nothing. It is like it is sometimes. They have a lot of machines. But I knew from the first second that I had nothing, unfortunately I was not the only one. Afterwards, everybody knew it!&rdquo;
